label: Data set
definition: A data set that is comprised of certain data items.|A data set that is the (direct) output of some planned process.
definition source: Source document defining the data set strucutre|Name of the author of the ontology extension
example of usage: The output produced by some research routine.|The output produced by some software application.
editor note: Some internal comment among contributors to the ontology extension.|Some comment that will not be part of the published version of the ontology.
curator note: Some administrative comment by a curator of the ontology extension.|Some administrative comment that is of use for a curator but not for a user.

label: Anatomical data set
definition: A data set that is about some anatomical entity.
example of usage: Collection of age-at-death estimates based on cranial suture obliteration.
editor note: This class is exclusively defined to demonstrate how the template works.

label: Output of a process
definition: A data set that is created by some planned process.
example of usage: The results of a standardised estimation of age-at-death based on cranial suture obliteration.
editor note: This class is exclusively defined to demonstrate how the template works.

label: Set of average values
definition: A data set that contains average values.
example of usage: A data set of average frequencies of observed pathological lesions in a number of populations.
editor note: This class is exclusively defined to demonstrate how the template works.
